TERMS AND CONDITIONS

1. Definitions

   "Software" means the R1 Control source code, binaries, documentation,
   and all associated files in this repository.

   "Internal Use" means running or using the Software for personal or
   internal business purposes — including use by employees, contractors,
   or developers on work machines or in a work context — where the
   Software is not distributed to end users outside your organization
   and is not incorporated into a product or service offered to others.

   "Commercial Distribution" means distributing, selling, licensing,
   sublicensing, or providing access to the Software — or any product,
   service, or tool that incorporates it — to third parties in exchange
   for revenue, compensation, or commercial advantage.

   "Closed-Source Distribution" means distributing the Software, or
   any derivative work, without making the complete corresponding
   source code publicly available under the terms of this License.

2. Grant of Rights

   Subject to the conditions in Section 3, HopIT grants you a
   worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive license to:

   a. Use and run the Software for any purpose, including Internal Use
      in a personal or commercial/professional setting.
      (Example: a developer running R1 Control at their desk at work
      is explicitly permitted at no cost.)

   b. Modify the Software and create derivative works.

   c. Distribute the Software or derivative works, provided that:
      i.  This License and the original copyright notice are preserved
          in all copies and substantial portions.
      ii. Any publicly distributed derivative work is made available
          under the terms of this License (same license, open source).
      iii.The following attribution is clearly displayed in the
          product, documentation, or About screen:
          "Based on R1 Control by HopIT (https://hopit.co)"

3. Restrictions

   The following require a separate written Commercial License
   Agreement from HopIT:

   a. Commercial Distribution — packaging, bundling, or incorporating
      the Software into a product or service offered to third parties,
      whether for payment or as part of a commercial offering.
      (Example: shipping R1 Control inside your own app, or offering
      it as part of a paid service, requires a commercial license.)

   b. Closed-Source Distribution — distributing the Software or a
      derivative work without releasing the full source code under
      this License.

   c. Removing or obscuring this License, the copyright notice, or
      the attribution requirement in Section 2(c)(iii).

4. Commercial Licensing

